<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 6:18PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A gusty rain shower will impact portions of southeastern Madison,
southeastern Beaverhead and southern Gallatin Counties through 700
PM MDT...
At 616 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles north of Monida, or 29 miles northwest of Idmon, moving east at
40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Monida, Cameron, Raynolds Pass and Monida Pass.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 1  and 8 .
Highway 287 between mile markers 1  and 5 , and between mile markers
1  and 40.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
